g.text: Padlocked Door: This door has been closed with a padlock. A chalk-drawn number on the board says #11.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Why would we want to break into some random citizen's apartment?"
You: "I don't know, just seems like something we could do."
Rhetoric: There's so much he could say right now, but he knows it wouldn't make much of a difference.
Kim Kitsuragi: He takes a closer look at the lock. "I supposed if one were *committed* to it, there's a pair of chaincutters in the Kineema."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant looks at you for a long moment, then blinks once...
Kim Kitsuragi: "I believe it's the *shackle* you mean to cut, detective." The lieutenant points to the corroded loop with a gloved finger.
Empathy: He's just trying to help, don't take it... bad. Relax.
You: "Don't you think that's what I'm *trying* to do?"
You: Use the chaincutters to cut through the padlock.
You: "Time for a little snip-snip!" (Do hand-scissors.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "You seem committed to it, so go on."
Interfacing: A lock blocks your path! You might have use for one of those standard police devices for cutting chains. Something that may be found in an RCM motor carriage...
Interfacing: The shackle snaps like a twig and the lock falls to the floor with a little thud. It should be possible to enter now...
Interfacing: What are you doing? You need to get your tools out, man.
Interfacing: What are you doing? You're trying to cut the body of the lock with the chaincutters and it's really not working.
You: "We could use some chaincutters here to cut the shackle."
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant doesn't say a word, his face wiped clear of any emotion.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Perhaps you should give it another go?"
Interfacing: Better whip out those cutters... you won't get very far otherwise.
Padlocked Door: It's a solid lump of metal, but the shackle is deeply corroded -- a solid pair of chaincutters would make short work of it.
Interfacing: Yes! Get those cutters in there and *snip* away. This weak chain is no match for your might.
Kim Kitsuragi: The lieutenant is concentrated on the hallway, scanning both ways for any approachers.
